<Docs title="Built-in Tools" description="Reference documentation for all of Clarissa's built-in tools">
  <h1>Built-in Tools</h1>
  <p>
    Clarissa comes with a comprehensive set of tools for file operations, Git integration, 
    system commands, and web access. Tools that could be destructive require confirmation before execution.
  </p>

  <h2>File Operations</h2>
  <table>
    <thead>
      <tr>
        <th>Tool</th>
        <th>Description</th>
      </tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr>
        <td><code>read_file</code></td>
        <td>View files with line numbers and range support</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><code>write_file</code></td>
        <td>Create or overwrite files</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><code>patch_file</code></td>
        <td>String replacement editing (str-replace style)</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><code>list_directory</code></td>
        <td>Tree view with filtering</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><code>search_files</code></td>
        <td>Regex search across files (grep-like)</td>
      </tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>

